      <div class="msgContentFrame">Nitpicky me...it's Ul'dah, not Uldar.  Uldar is too close to Ulduar which was one of my least favorite raids in WoW. <br /> <br />You can repair your own gear if you have the necessary DoH class ranked up to the point where you can repair it.  Leather gear typically requires Tanner.  Cloth gear typically requires Weaver.  Mail/plate gear requires armorer, etc.  You repair your gear by equipping the tools for the necessary DoH class and then selecting the item to be repaired from your inventory.  You then click the &quot;repair&quot; button that shows up and it will bring up a slightly modified version of the synthesis window where you select the repair materials and then main or off hand.  If you're not the right DoH class to perform the repairs, it will tell you and won't bring up the synthesis window.  If you're the right class but not high enough skill, it will tell you after you select main/offhand tool that you're not high enough. <br /> <br />For locations of NPCs, you're better off asking this stuff in-game where people can actually direct you.  For the record, he's across from the chocobo at the main gate.</div>
